summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from James C. Ford and Mary E. Ford, his wife, to the City of Seattle, dated the 28th day of August, 1907, to a certain portion or parcel of land lying in Tract 139 of the Replat of John J. McGilvra's Addition to the City of Seattle, and Blocks 13, 14, 18, 20, 21, 22, 23, 24, 25, 26, 27, 28 and 29 and the south half of 19 of John J. McGilvra's Second Addition to the City of Seattle.
